Unable to hit the 'x' or close button of the error message
----------------------------------------------------------
Summary:
When opening the webpage in a mobile device, right after making a mistake at inputting the username and password, I find it impossible to click or tap the close button of the error message as the link to the github repo overlaps the close button.

Setup:
1. http://the-internet.herokuapp.com/login
2. Right click then click inspect
3. Click dropdown Responsive
4. Choose any mobile device.

Steps:
1. Click the username input field.
2. Input a wrong username.
3. Click the password input field.
4. Input a wrong password.
5. Click the 'x' button at the end of the error message.


Expected Result:
Closes the error message while staying at the page.

Actual Result:
It opens a new web page https://github.com/saucelabs/the-internet instead.
